6673 /* Important note concerning multiple encryption calls
6674  * If the firmware is already handling any crypto operation, and another task
6675  * requests another crypto operation, the firmware will respond with a
6676  * DM_CRYPTO_BUSY message. The user will have to handle this response and send
6677  * their request at a later time.
6678  *
6679  * It is important to note that whenever data is passed to any of the crypto
6680  * functions as an array, the endianness of the word groups must be flipped.
6681  * Essentially, the least significant word must be the array's zero-th element,
6682  * and the most significant word must be the array's last element.
6683  *
6684  * Consequently, the data returned by these functions also has its endianness
6685  * flipped in the same way. However, in addition to endianness, the sequence of
6686  * octets within each word is also flipped, so if the returned value's most
6687  * significant word is 88d4, the returned array's zero-th element with be d488.
6688  */
